## Phase 3 — Immutable Accounting Safety

> **Risk: Medium** | **Schema change: Yes**

### Architecture Decision

The existing `Settlement` model already has `CalculatorVersion` and `VehicleNumberSnapshot` / `DriverNameSnapshot`. We extend it with:

| New Field | Type | Purpose |
|-----------|------|---------|
| `CalculationHash` | `TEXT` | SHA-256 of the canonical calculation inputs — detects data tampering |
| `RevisionNumber` | `INTEGER` | 0 = original, increments on each edit |
| `FormulaVersion` | `INTEGER` | Mirrors `SettlementCalculator.CurrentVersion` at time of save |

### Hash Input (deterministic, canonical)
```
SHA-256( "{Date:yyyyMMdd}|{DriverId}|{VehicleId}|{TotalIncome:F2}|
          {DriverShare:F2}|{OwnerCngShare:F2}|{TotalOwnerExpenses:F2}|
          {NetDriverPayable:F2}|{CalculatorVersion}" )
```

**Why this matters:** If any financial field is tampered (e.g., direct SQLite edit), the hash will mismatch. The audit view shows a ⚠ flag.

### New Files

#### [NEW] `Database/Migrations/Migration_008_AddSettlementIntegrity.cs`
```sql
