## Phase 1 — OEM Device Hardening

> **Risk: Low** | **Schema change: No**

### Xiaomi / Redmi
- **AutoStart permission:** Show one-time advisory dialog on first launch explaining the user must enable AutoStart in MIUI settings for background backup to work
- **SQLite busy timeout:** Increase from default 0ms → 3000ms via `PRAGMA busy_timeout = 3000` in `DatabaseService`
- **Background process kill:** `BackupService.AutoBackupIfNeededAsync` already has try/catch — confirm it handles `OperationCanceledException`

### Samsung One UI 6+
- **DeX mode:** `onConfigurationChanged` — MAUI handles this via shell navigation, no action needed
- **Secure Folder:** APP install in Secure Folder requires separate APK install — document in release notes

### Realme / Oppo ColorOS
- **Permission auto-reset:** VIBRATE permission now declared (previous fix). Storage permission may be auto-revoked after 3 months of no use — `BackupService` already falls back to app-private directory

### All OEMs — Battery Optimization
- **First launch:** Show `Settings → Battery → DriverLedger → Unrestricted` advisory using `Intent.ActionRequestIgnoreBatteryOptimizations` (Android 6+)

