## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Backup encryption key derivation:** The AES-256-GCM key is derived from the owner's company name + device install ID via PBKDF2. This means if the user reinstalls the app on a new device, backups from the old device **cannot be restored** without the original company name. Is this acceptable, or should we add a user-defined backup password?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Monthly PDF report scope:** `GenerateVehicleMonthlyProfitAsync(int year, int month)` — should this show ALL vehicles, or one vehicle at a time? The existing `IPdfService` signature takes `year` and `month` but no vehicle ID.

> [!NOTE]
> **Root detection action:** The plan shows a warning advisory on rooted devices, NOT a block. Blocking would prevent legitimate users who root their phones for legitimate reasons. Confirm this is acceptable.

